<p>Technical Information (for support personnel)</p>
<ul>
<li>Go to <a href="http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?linkid=8180">Microsoft Product Support Services</a> and perform a title search for the words <b>HTTP</b> and <b>401</b>.</li>
<li>Open <b>IIS Help</b>, which is accessible in IIS Manager (inetmgr),
 and search for topics titled <b>Configuring ISAPI Extensions</b>, and <b>About Custom Error Messages</b>.</li>
<li>In the IIS Software Development Kit (SDK) or at the <a href="http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=8181">MSDN Online Library</a>, search for topics titled <b>Developing ISAPI Extensions</b>, <b>ISAPI and CGI</b>, and <b>Debugging ISAPI Extensions and Filters</b>.</li>
</ul>

<h2>HTTP Error 401.5 - Unauthorized: Authorization failed by an ISAPI/CGI application.<br>Internet Information Services (IIS)</h2>
<hr>
<p>Technical Information (for support personnel)</p>
<ul>
<li>Go to <a href="http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?linkid=8180">Microsoft Product Support Services</a> and perform a title search for the words <b>HTTP</b> and <b>401</b>.</li>
<li>Open <b>IIS Help</b>, which is accessible in IIS Manager (inetmgr),
 and search for topics titled <b>Configuring ISAPI Extensions</b>, and <b>About Custom Error Messages</b>.</li>
<li>In the IIS Software Development Kit (SDK) or at the <a href="http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=8181">MSDN Online Library</a>, search for topics titled <b>Developing ISAPI Extensions</b>, <b>ISAPI and CGI</b>, and <b>Debugging ISAPI Extensions and Filters</b>.</li>
</ul>
